sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Frontend as React Frontend<br/>(Zustand + React Query)
    participant API as FastAPI Backend<br/>(cameras router)
    participant GIS as GIS Service<br/>(Shapely + pyproj)
    participant DB as MongoDB<br/>(camera_instances)
    participant WS as WebSocket Manager

    User->>Frontend: Drops camera on map / edits bearing
    Frontend->>Frontend: 300ms debounce
    Frontend->>API: POST /api/v1/projects/{id}/cameras<br/>{ model_id, position, bearing, overrides }

    API->>DB: Fetch CameraModel (fov_angle, max_range, min_range)
    DB-->>API: CameraModel document

    API->>GIS: compute_fov_polygon(lat, lng, bearing,<br/>fov_angle, max_range, min_range)
    GIS->>GIS: Geodesic projection via pyproj<br/>Build 4-point polygon:<br/>Origin → Left → Arc Mid → Right
    GIS-->>API: GeoJSON Polygon

    API->>DB: Insert / Update CameraInstance<br/>{ ...fields, fov_geojson }
    DB-->>API: Saved CameraInstance

    API->>WS: broadcast camera_added / camera_updated<br/>to project room (exclude originator)
    WS-->>Frontend: Broadcast to other connected editors

    API-->>Frontend: 200 OK — full CameraInstance with fov_geojson
    Frontend->>Frontend: Update cameraSlice in Zustand
    Frontend->>Frontend: Re-render GeoJSON layer on Leaflet map